&lt;DIV&gt;I was using my newly acquired Wrack Undead AA (upgrade to TU3 in the PoP abilities AA list) and I noticed two things:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) the DoT does indeed work over 6 ticks (1st when it is cast and for 5 ticks after that)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) the "4th level" does 500/tick which is a 200/tick jump from TU3.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Now for an opinion:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The 32k DD proc rate is too low.&amp;nbsp; That's 1 in 20. that's an average or one proc every 100 minutes or ~1 proc every DOD mission.&amp;nbsp;With all the new undead in DOD I am very glad that the TU AA was altered to its current state (the old version would have been massively exploited), but an increase to the proc chance for each level you "purchase" would not be outta line IMO.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
