    <item>
      <title>Re: New Turn Undead maxes out at 500dmg/tick? Not acceptable!!!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10879#M10879</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;All I can say is that I'm disappointed that with the discussion here and the declaration that Turn Undead would be made something useful and valuable to all clerics, that it has instead been thrust back at us in an altered state without much attention paid to our feedback and, apparently, considered a solved problem.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Has there been any feedback from the developers since the original discussion? Not that I've seen.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It's a pity that game changes like this one all to well follow the "EQ Cycle" as I describe it.&amp;nbsp; First there are proposed changes with much feedback from the developers and community.&amp;nbsp; Lots of changes are discussed.&amp;nbsp; A few minor ones are implemented while others are reportedly being worked on.&amp;nbsp; Feedback levels fall off.&amp;nbsp; A holiday / fan faire / expansion break looms, and attention is diverted from all other concerns.&amp;nbsp; Feedback becomes negligible.&amp;nbsp; The holiday passes, the fan faire concludes, or the expansion is released, and then all attention is focused now onto new things... and the old concerns, which originally had so much feedback and promise, are shelved.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Oh, they might not be totally ignored, but they're addressed at the sluglike rate which ensures that many of them will never see resolution, because the cycle repeats itself again. There's always another fan faire, or another holiday, or another expansion looming on the horizon, and in reality, the finite lifespan of EQ and the drive to expand will ensure the snowball effect continues, always gathering problems and never stopping to address them.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What does that mean? A whole lot of drivel, really.&amp;nbsp; It means if you think about it too long, you write long, meandering posts like this one... and then you realize that they're pointless, and you snap out of your gloom, and you go and play the game anyway because it's fun most of the time, and your friends are there.&amp;nbsp; You sigh wistfully as you click your Turn Undead ability on a zombie, and you pray that the 32k effect will happen, because otherwise the effect is pretty minor.&amp;nbsp; Of course, the 32k doesn't happen, so you heal, or you cast a nuke spell (oops, nuke critted for 4024.. while my turn undead did 2500 damage).. and you heal some more.. and five minutes goes by and you face another undead.. and you fail the 32k.. and you try again.. and again... and again...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;And then you are done your adventure, and heading back to the Plane of Knowledge and you come across a decaying skeleton.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;32k, naturally.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
