      <title>Re: New Turn Undead maxes out at 500dmg/tick? Not acceptable!!!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9832#M9832</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;gt;Keep in mind, Clerics used the be the game's "Undead Wizards," because our undead nukes were comparable to wizard nukes of the same level.&amp;nbsp;Now their nuke can easily crit for 8k at lvl 70, but our undead nukes are about the same as our normal nukes for a little less mana, barely criting for 3k?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;To be honest, they weren't really ever all that comparable. The relative position of cleric undead nukes vs wizard nukes hasn't really changed that much. Looking at the end levels over time, at 50, Ice Comet was 1120 and Banish Undead was 466 (~42%). At level 60, Sunstrike was 1615 and Exile Undead was 725 (~44%). At 65, Strike of Solusek was 2740 and&amp;nbsp;Destroy Undead was 1200 (~44%). At 70, Corona Flare is 3770 and Desolate Undead is 1610 (~43%). So, it looks like they have stayed pretty much the same in relative damage. Since they don't usually give new undead nukes when the end levels change, wizard nukes have always&amp;nbsp;tended to go up more relative to the undead nukes the longer you stay at a given level cap. And Ancient spells have also pretty much always widened the gap. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
